registrationMode.description: determine how the events are processed as well as how the reports are aggregated and sliced

protocol.description: protocols used to help determine how the events are processed as well as how the reports are aggregated and sliced

calendarType.description: this defines calendar type for scheduling

meetingCategory.description: this defines meeting categories for scheduling

identifiers.description:
Base type for the various identifiers used to connect the dots.
In general, these should be populated whenever possible. Subtypes may make a particular key required.

cpaasIdentifiers.description:
Set of identifiers dedicated to CPaaS clients
In general, these should be populated whenever possible. Subtypes may make a particular key required.

items.description: specific error detected by originator of event

clientMediaError.description: media quality error report such as no media or drop out

endTrigger.description: End Trigger - indicate how the call was ended from client. Set in end of call events such as client.call.end, client.call.aborted

oldOrigin.description: Information about the sender of the event

upgradeChannel.description: Will be used as a label for client software status

instanceId.description: Identifier for a particular instance of a service, such as a particular linus

clientType.description: this defines the major client types

subClientType.description: this defines the sub types of clients

schedulingClientType.description: this defines the major client types for scheduling

clientVersionStatus.description: this defines the client version status. Determined by call analyzer based on client major version

cpuInfo.description: This object defines the fields related to the CPU being used by the emitter of the event

videoDisplayMode.description: Video display mode currently in use

videoRenderType.description: this defines the video render type of meetings

launch32BitsReason.description: this defines launch 32 bits client reason

mediaMetadata.description: metadata associated with emitter of the event. This data is included only in the first emitted for a given call and does not need to be repeated with each event.

eventData.description: data define for background noise removal event

breakoutSessionSummaryInfo.description: Details of breakout session information, sent after end of breakout session

actionData.description: data define for background noise removal action

eventData.description: data define for background noise removal event

embeddedBrowserObject.description: call embedded browser object result, if failed, will populate error at Error item

downloadInfo.description: data define for download detail data

mediaQualityMetadata.description: The metadata associated with the emitter of the event.  This data is separate from the source metadata and must be emitted with every event.

memoryUsage.description: this object defines the memory related fields that are tracked in media quality events and reports

batteryHealth.description: Indicates battery health. See https://developer.android.com/reference/android/os/BatteryManager for more information.

batteryPlugged.description: Provides visibility in charger type in use

darwinThermalState.description: Provides visibility of customer experience in limited thermal headroom environments on Apple devices. See https://developer.apple.com/documentation/foundation/processinfo/thermalstate for more information.

androidThermalStatus.description: Indicates thermal status on Android devices. See https://developer.android.com/ndk/reference/group/thermal for more information.

cpuInfo.description: This object defines the fields related to the CPU being used by the emitter of the event

defaultGpuInfo.description: This object defines the fields related to the GPU being used by the emitter of the event

items.description: This object defines the fields related to the GPU being used by the emitter of the event

roomType.description: provisioning room type for CE devices

mercuryLatencyAggregates.description: Aggregated information for mercury latency metric

mercuryMaxLatency.description: Maximum latency information during a meting

wxcCallingDelay.description: This object tracks the call setup time and call setup failure time. All delay attributes are in milliseconds.

callSetupTime.description: firstAudioPacketReceivedTime - joinCallTime - alertToAnswered (for Outgoing) OR firstAudioPacketReceivedTime (for Incoming, call setup time is from user press accept button to the first audio data received)

joinCallTime.description: When the incoming call accept handling is started Or when the user initiate outgoing call.

connectSipTime.description: When the Mobile client start the SIP registration.

sipConnectedTime.description: When the Mobile client sip registration is ready.

startAudioSDPSetupTime.description: When the client start initialization of the WME to get the required data for Audio SDP.

audioSDPReadyTime.description: WME provided the required data for the SDP (Audio codecs, Start the listener and return the port, Acquire ICE candidates for audio).

startVideoSDPSetupTime.description: When the client start initialisation of the WME to get the required data for Video SDP.

videoSDPReadyTime.description: WME provided the required data for the SDP (Video codecs, Start the listener and return the port, Acquire ICE candidates for video).

SDPReadyTime.description: The bigger one between audioSDPReadyTime and videoSDPReadyTime.

startLocalAudioTrackTime.description: Before wmeTrack->start() for the local audio track.

localAudioTrackStartedTime.description: After wmeTrack->start() for the local audio track.

startRemoteAudioTrackTime.description: Before wmeTrack->start() for the remote audio track.

remoteAudioTrackStartedTime.description: After wmeTrack->start() for the local audio track.

startLocalVideoTrackTime.description: Before wmeTrack->start() for the local video track.

localVideoTrackStartedTime.description: After wmeTrack->start() for the local video track.

startRemoteVideoTrackTime.description: Before wmeTrack->start() for the remote video track.

remoteVideoTrackStartedTime.description: After wmeTrack->start() for the remote video track.

startSipInviteTime.description: Client send SIP INVITE. For outgoing and incoming calls on mobile and outgoing only on desktop.

applyAudioSDPTime.description: For outgoing calls 200OK with SDP is received. For incoming calls ACK of local SDP is received. Then all data from the SDP is provided to the WME.

callIsConnectedTime.description: The time when the call is successfully established.

firstAudioPacketSentTime.description: First audio packet is captured from microphone and sent to the remote.

firstAudioPacketReceivedTime.description: First audio packet from the remote side is received and send to the sound interface.

firstVideoPacketSentTime.description: First packet is captured from the camera and sent to the remote side.

firstVideoPacketReceivedTime.description: First packet is received from the remote side and sent to the renderer.

iosAudioSessionActiveTime.description: iOS specific. The audio session is activated.

switchedToForegroundTime.description: If the call was started in background then when the user unlocks the screen the time is recorded. At this time the camera will be opened. Meaningful only on iOS.

callDuration.description: The time between call join and call close.

audioCaptureFirstSpeechTime.description: Timestamp in milliseconds of first VAD (voice activity detection) detected for capturer

audioPlaybackFirstSpeechTime.description: Timestamp in milliseconds of first WmeMediaEngineEventType_Audio_Processing_NotifyFirstSpeech. First time when VAD (voice activity detection) event is sent from WME for playback

mediaDeviceErrorStatistics.description: This object tracks the Audio device error statistics

captureRecoveryCount.description: Number of WmeMediaEngineEventType_Audio_DeviceStatus_Capture_DataAvailable during the call after WmeMediaEngineEventType_Audio_DeviceStatus_Capture_NoDataTimeout

firstCaptureNoDataRecovery.description: Timestamp in milliseconds of first WmeMediaEngineEventType_Audio_DeviceStatus_Capture_DataAvailable after WmeMediaEngineEventType_Audio_DeviceStatus_Capture_NoDataTimeout

playbackRecoveryCount.description: Number of WmeMediaEngineEventType_Audio_DeviceStatus_Playback_DataAvailable during the call after WmeMediaEngineEventType_Audio_DeviceStatus_Playback_NoDataTimeout

firstPlaybackNoDataRecovery.description: Timestamp in milliseconds of first WmeMediaEngineEventType_Audio_DeviceStatus_Playback_DataAvailable after WmeMediaEngineEventType_Audio_DeviceStatus_Playback_NoDataTimeout
